{"key":"processedPost-12783307","value":{"id":12783307,"first":12781837,"last":12783677,"when":1277215356,"utime":"06/22/10 05:02 PM","content":"I use filter patch bags for small batches.&nbsp; The water around it needs to boil for 20 minutes or so before the substrate in the bag begins to come up to temperature.&nbsp; At around 120F, shut off the stove and see where the substrate stabilizes at.&nbsp; You'll probably need to turn the stove back on to regulate temperature after a time, but the idea is that in the center of the bag, your casing or substrate mix remains at 140F to 160F for an hour.<br />Larger batches, I do outdoors with steam in a 55 gallon drum, unless it's straw which I put directly into the pasteurization water.<br />RR","title":"Re: trouble pasteurizing"}}